<subSubSection id="C36D6550FFCD8F55FF09FEBDFB1C2DC4" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1095" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094" type="key">
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09FEBDFD0D2E1C" blockId="4.[160,661,334,358]" box="[160,661,334,358]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FF09FEBDFD0D2E1C" bold="true" box="[160,661,334,358]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
Key to the species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D58FFCD8F54FD83FEBDFD0D2E1C" authorityName="Pereira and Martinez" authorityYear="1960" box="[554,661,334,358]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Isocopris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Isocopris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<key id="FFE661EAFFCD8F55FF09FE71FB1C2DC4" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1095" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyStep id="30832E7EFFCD8F54FF09FE71FB1C2DF0" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09FE71FB1C2D78" blockId="4.[160,1156,386,650]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCD8F54FF09FE71FB1C2D78" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
1. Pronotum abruptly vertical above the head, superiorly with a pair of transverse humps. Male with a cephalic horn always flanked by two low and transverse carinae; female with a cephalic carina tuberculate at middle. Large-sized species, body length&gt; 
<quantity id="4C8F9B3EFFCD8F54FE95FE19FE1B2D78" box="[316,387,490,514]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094" unit="mm" value="22.0">22 mm</quantity>
................................................................................................................................... 2.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09FDF9FB1C2DF0" blockId="4.[160,1156,386,650]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCD8F54FF09FDF9FB1C2DF0" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
1' Pronotum simply convex, never with distinct humps on the superior side. Male either with a simple and conical horn or with a transverse and strong carina; female with either a cephalic horn or carina, but never tuberculate at middle. Medium-sized species, body length &lt;
<quantity id="4C8F9B3EFFCD8F54FE77FD81FDB62DF0" box="[478,558,626,650]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094" unit="mm" value="22.0">22 mm</quantity>
..................................................................................................... 3.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30832E7EFFCD8F54FF09FD59FB1C2BF8" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09FD59FB1C2C15" blockId="4.[160,1156,682,1154]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCD8F54FF09FD59FB1C2C15" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
2. Clypeus wide and evenly curved, slightly sinuated at middle, male with cephalic horn cylindrical to conical (from above), frontal side of the horn always finely wrinkled; female with cephalic carina on the fronto-clypeal region, anteromedial region of pronotum feebly excavated, pronotal protuberance very weak (
<figureCitation id="134C2A5EFFCD8F54FBAFFCE1FBC52C50" box="[1030,1117,786,810]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="6.[161,226,1421,1444]" captionTargetBox="[164,1145,145,1389]" captionTargetId="figure-82@6.[164,1153,140,1390]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 1. Isocopris inhiatus. (a–b) Dorsal habitus of male and female. (c–d) Dorsal and lateral side of the parameres. (e–f) Lamella copulatrix and secondary accessory lamella." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181294/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(a 
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FBDFFCE1FB1B2C50" box="[1142,1155,786,810]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">–</emphasis>
b)). Anterior pronotal bead simple, metasternal surface completely covered by long and straight orange hairs. 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCD8F54FE56FCA4FDA62C15" box="[511,574,855,879]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCD8F54FDE3FCA4FD282C15" box="[586,688,855,879]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Argentina</collectingCountry>
.................... .................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D58FFCD8F54FC0EFCA5FB182C15" authority="(Germar)" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[935,1152,854,879]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Isocopris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inhiatus">
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FC0EFCA5FB8B2C15" box="[935,1043,854,879]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">I. inhiatus</emphasis>
(Germar)
</taxonomicName>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09FC84FB1C2BF8" blockId="4.[160,1156,682,1154]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCD8F54FF09FC84FB1C2BF8" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
2' Clypeus elongated forward and clearly narrower at middle, lateral margins straight, male with cephalic horn rectangular and transversally elongated, frontal side of the horn smooth to finely punctuated; female with cephalic carina between eyes, anteromedial region of the pronotum distinctly excavated, pronotal humps distinct (
<figureCitation id="134C2A5EFFCD8F54FE1FFBF1FD8D2B60" box="[438,533,1026,1050]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[161,226,1400,1423]" captionTargetBox="[165,1151,149,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-42@7.[164,1153,145,1369]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Isocopris hypocrita. (a–b) Dorsal habitus of male and female. (c–d) Dorsal and lateral side of the parameres. (e–f) Lamella copulatrix and secondary accessory lamella." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181296/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Figure 2</figureCitation>
(a 
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FD83FBF1FDAF2B60" box="[554,567,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">–</emphasis>
b)). Anterior pronotal bead slightly concave at the middle of the posterior margin, metasternum with long hairs along the inner side of mesocoxae, metasternal disc bare. 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCD8F54FD24FBB4FD5B2B25" box="[653,707,1095,1119]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Brazil</collectingCountry>
............................................................................ ................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D58FFCD8F54FD04FB9AFC1D2BF8" authority="(Lucas)" authorityName="Rossini &amp; Vaz-de-Mello" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Rossini &amp; Vaz-de-Mello" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[685,901,1129,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Isocopris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypocrita" status="comb. nov., stat. rev.">
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FD04FB9AFCB32BF8" box="[685,811,1129,1154]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">I. hypocrita</emphasis>
(Lucas)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23057B2FFCD8F54FC26FB99FB1C2BF8" box="[911,1156,1130,1154]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">comb. nov., stat. rev.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30832E7EFFCD8F54FF09FB51FB1C2AB6" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09FB51FB1C2A3E" blockId="4.[160,1156,1186,1484]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCD8F54FF09FB51FB1C2A3E" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
3. Both sexes with a strong fronto-clypeal carina flanked by two hump-like weak tubercles, carina acuminated on both sides in male, straight in female, frons deeply depressed (
<figureCitation id="134C2A5EFFCD8F54FEFDFB14FE372B85" box="[340,431,1255,1279]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="10.[161,226,1203,1226]" captionTargetBox="[179,1143,152,1172]" captionTargetId="figure-116@10.[164,1153,144,1172]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figure 5. Isocopris foveolatus. (a–b) Dorsal habitus of male and female. (c–d) Dorsal and lateral side of the parameres." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181302" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181302/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Figure 5</figureCitation>
(a 
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FE6AFB14FE482B85" box="[451,464,1255,1279]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">–</emphasis>
b)). Margin of the head distinctly notched at the clypeo-genal junction, body completely black, head and pronotum shining, elytra more opaque. 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCD8F54FF7BFADFFE9F2A3E" box="[210,263,1324,1348]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Brazil</collectingCountry>
................................................... ................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D58FFCD8F54FCFCFAD8FB182A3E" authority="(Luederwaldt)" baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[853,1152,1323,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Isocopris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveolatus">
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FCFCFAD8FC412A3E" box="[853,985,1323,1348]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">I. foveolatus</emphasis>
(Luederwaldt)
</taxonomicName>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09FABFFB1C2AB6" blockId="4.[160,1156,1186,1484]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCD8F54FF09FABFFB1C2AB6" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">3' Both sexes with a conical cephalic horn, margin of the head either notched or angulated (genal margin wider than clypeus) at the clypeo-genal junction, frons either depressed or normal, clypeus weakly to distinctly reflexed at middle ............................................................................................................................................... 4.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30832E7EFFCD8F54FF09FA1FFB1C29D5" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09FA1FFB1C2930" blockId="4.[160,1156,1516,1711]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCD8F54FF09FA1FFB1C2930" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
4. Fore tibia with an inner-apical projection, tooth-like and directed inward, last protarsal segment strongly enlarged at the apex, tarsal claws very long and strongly folded (
<figureCitation id="134C2A5EFFCD8F54FE83F9C1FE102930" box="[298,392,1586,1610]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="11.[162,227,1257,1280]" captionTargetBox="[171,1150,141,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-167@11.[165,1154,138,1227]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 6. Isocopris tarsalis. (a–b) Dorsal habitus of male and female. (c–d) Dorsal and lateral side of the parameres. (e) Tarsal claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181304" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181304/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(a 
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FE35F9C2FE312933" box="[412,425,1585,1609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">–</emphasis>
b, e)). 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCD8F54FE5BF9C1FDB02930" box="[498,552,1586,1610]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">Brazil</collectingCountry>
............................ ............................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D58FFCD8F54FCD1F9C2FB182930" authority="(Luederwaldt)" baseAuthorityName="Luederwaldt" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[888,1152,1585,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Isocopris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCD8F54FCD1F9C2FC422930" box="[888,986,1585,1610]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">I. tarsalis</emphasis>
(Luederwaldt)
</taxonomicName>
.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCD8F54FF09F9A1FB1C29D5" blockId="4.[160,1156,1516,1711]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCD8F54FF09F9A1FB1C29D5" pageId="4" pageNumber="1094">4' Fore tibia either normal or with an inner-apical projection directed forward, last protarsal segment normal and never strongly enlarged, tarsal claws short and weakly curved....................................................................................................................................... 5.</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30832E7EFFCC8F55FF09FF7DFB1C2E84" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCC8F55FF09FF7DFB1C2E2E" blockId="5.[160,1156,142,510]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCC8F55FF09FF7DFB1C2E2E" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
5. Clypeus acuminate and sides feebly curved, weakly reflexed and distinctly sinuated at middle, with two obtuse teeth, head of both sexes with three conical tubercles, central tubercle stronger, lateral ones slightly backward, frons not depressed. Apical spur of the fore tibia with superior margin normal. Body black, elytra opaque to feebly shining and completely sericeous. 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCC8F55FD6AFEEAFD672E4B" box="[707,767,281,305]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(only known of north of 
<collectingRegion id="49B3F839FFCC8F55FBE8FEEAFE842E2E" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
), dry forest.............................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D58FFCC8F55FC19FEC8FBBA2E2E" authority="Rossini &amp; Vaz-de-Mello, 2017" authorityName="Rossini &amp; Vaz-de-Mello" authorityYear="2017" box="[944,1058,315,340]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Isocopris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xacriaba" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCC8F55FC19FEC8FBBA2E2E" box="[944,1058,315,340]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">I. xacriaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23057B2FFCC8F55FB82FECFFB1C2E2E" box="[1067,1156,316,340]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCC8F55FF09FEA8FB1C2E84" blockId="5.[160,1156,142,510]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCC8F55FF09FEA8FB1C2E84" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
5' Clypeus with sides sinuated, strongly reflexed at middle, either transversally truncated or weakly sinuated, both sexes with a central conical horn flanked by two weak hump-like tubercles, frons slightly to distinctly depressed. Apical spur of the fore tibia with superior margin bifid (
<figureCitation id="134C2A5EFFCC8F55FDDFFE30FD4B2EA1" box="[630,723,451,475]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="8.[163,228,1143,1166]" captionTargetBox="[175,1146,139,1109]" captionTargetId="figure-133@8.[165,1154,138,1113]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 3. Isocopris imitator. (a, d) Dorsal habitus of male and female. (b–c) Details of the pronotal and elytral punctuation. (e–f) Dorsal and lateral side of the parameres. (g) Lamella copulatrix. (h) Apical spur of the fore tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181298" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181298/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(h)). Body completely shining, black to brownish. Known of Amazon and dry forests ........................................................................ 6.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30832E7EFFCC8F55FF09FDEDFB1C2DC4" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCC8F55FF09FDEDFB1C2D23" blockId="5.[160,1156,542,702]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCC8F55FF09FDEDFB1C2D23" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
6. Pronotum and elytra with a dense and shallow punctuation evenly distributed (
<figureCitation id="134C2A5EFFCC8F55FF70FDB2FEA02D23" box="[217,312,577,601]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="8.[163,228,1143,1166]" captionTargetBox="[175,1146,139,1109]" captionTargetId="figure-133@8.[165,1154,138,1113]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 3. Isocopris imitator. (a, d) Dorsal habitus of male and female. (b–c) Details of the pronotal and elytral punctuation. (e–f) Dorsal and lateral side of the parameres. (g) Lamella copulatrix. (h) Apical spur of the fore tibia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181298" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181298/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">Figure 3</figureCitation>
(b 
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCC8F55FEE7FDB2FEC32D23" box="[334,347,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">–</emphasis>
c)). Size of 
<quantity id="4C8F9B3EFFCC8F55FE70FDB2FDCC2D23" box="[473,596,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095" unit="mm" value="18.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="15.0">
15 
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCC8F55FE5DFDB2FD992D23" box="[500,513,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">–</emphasis>
22 mm
</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCC8F55FDC9FDB2FD0F2D23" box="[608,663,577,601]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">Brazil</collectingCountry>
...................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C774D58FFCC8F55FC8FFDB3FC642D23" authority="(Felsche)" authorityName="Rossini &amp; Vaz-de-Mello" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Rossini &amp; Vaz-de-Mello" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[806,1020,576,601]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitator" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCC8F55FC8FFDB3FC092D23" box="[806,913,576,601]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">I. imitator</emphasis>
(Felsche)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23057B2FFCC8F55FBACFDB2FB1C2D23" box="[1029,1156,577,601]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC836DBFFCC8F55FF09FD93FB1C2DC4" blockId="5.[160,1156,542,702]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
<keyLead id="308695EEFFCC8F55FF09FD93FB1C2DC4" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">
6' Pronotum and elytra with a very fine and inconspicuous punctuation (
<figureCitation id="134C2A5EFFCC8F55FC4AFD93FBD82D02" box="[995,1088,608,632]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="9.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[170,1142,153,1132]" captionTargetId="figure-174@9.[163,1152,149,1137]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 4. Isocopris nitidus. (a, d) Dorsal habitus of male and female. (b–c) Details of the pronotal and elytral punctuation. (e–f) Dorsal and lateral side of the parameres. (g) Lamella copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5181300" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5181300/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">Figure 4</figureCitation>
(b 
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCC8F55FBFCFD93FBFA2D02" box="[1109,1122,608,632]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">–</emphasis>
c)). Size of 
<quantity id="4C8F9B3EFFCC8F55FE8FFD70FE3A2DE1" box="[294,418,643,667]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095" unit="mm" value="15.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="12.0">
12 
<emphasis id="B903EAC9FFCC8F55FEE8FD70FED62DE1" box="[321,334,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">–</emphasis>
18 mm
</quantity>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCC8F55FE07FD70FDCC2DE1" box="[430,596,643,667]" name="French Guiana" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCC8F55FDC9FD70FD042DE1" box="[608,668,643,667]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F360764BFFCC8F55FD71FD70FC9C2DE1" box="[728,772,643,667]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="1095">Peru</collectingCountry>
.................................................................... .............................................................................. 
